 Condor:
Condor appeared in brigde and said to Maximal leader &quot;Condor reports, sir... What&#39;s the situation?&quot;
  Jonathan &lt;jhogan@...&gt; wrote: He slowly starts to move again. The legendary Autobot, who had descided to work on a Maximal ship, made his way to the bridge. {Talos}Bridge The maximal commander listened as the reports came in, the armory he imagined must have looked like a battle hit it. Sighing he righted himself in his chair more fully turning towards the two bots that had walked onto his bridge giving a nod of respect to Hot Rod, it had been a relative honor to serve alongside one of the more key figures in their peoples histories. The other seemed to imply he was a criminal of some sort, he didn&#39;t really care in any case. &quot;Armory is only shook up, but reports seem to say the thrusters are off line and quite frankly scrap. We need to get external sensors up and see just what kind of planet we&#39;ve crashed ourselves on, once we can see where the slag we are we can go from there...&quot; Turning he regarded the &#39;criminal&#39;, &quot;I don&#39;t know what in the Matrix you&#39;re talking about. You appear to believe you&#39;re in trouble with the law but at this point I don&#39;t give a slag what you&#39;ve done. This ship is in bad shape, we have a mission to complete and I don&#39;t have time to assign personnel to guard you in a brig.&quot;     Turning he looked the bot in the eye, &quot;Help Hot Rod get our sensors up and running or report yourself to the CR chambers on deck two if you&#39;re too injured to help. But if you plan on sticking around you&#39;re gonna help us, now get to it.&quot;     Swiveling in the chair he regarded the com, &quot;Icedemon and Archangel get started on repairs on either the computers or Comm systems. BlackKnight check the ship for any more bots whose comms might be down, injuries to the CR chambers those not functioning, as much as I hate to say it, we&#39;ll worry about later, priority on the operational first.&quot; Turning back to look out the shattered window he silently hoped Megatron was as bad off as they were, if the predicons launched a pre-emptive strike he doubted the ship could take a beating after the crash. Moving to the computers he began investigating the status of the frigates weapons and defense systems, they weren&#39;t priority one at the moment but he wanted at least something to re-assure the crew they weren&#39;t sitting blind and utterly defenseless.
